                          GAME SCENARIO
                          =============
  A Semi Overhead View Perspective " Space Fantasy Arcade Adventure "
  At present being Developed for " Amiga CD32/1200 with HD or CD Rom.
  The Adventure is set in the Future with the 4 main player characters
  being Mercanaries from the 21st century, who are Available for Hire.
  Main Employers are Policital Organisations but they have worked for
  Paramilitary Organisations on Past Missions.

                          GAME FEATURES
                          =============
  256 Colour Screens,80 in-game Screen Colors, 64 bit wide 16 color
  Sprites, 50hz 8 way scrolling,Digitised Speech & Sound Effects
  Action Packed Realistic Gameplay.


  " FTLOM DEMO "  is 1 Player. & You must choose "JACK TOWNSEND (c)
  as your Player Character. The reason for this is Code Size.
 (including all 4 characters &  vehicles would make this file even
  more massive.)
			INSTRUCTIONS
                        ============
  Pc Control -: is via joystick in port 2, to move pc, simply move
  joystick in the corresponding direction.
 
  Gun Control-: Press fire and hold for repeated fire (Auto-fire joystick
  is not recommended).
 
   Pick Up Item-: Run over item to collect.

                          GAME PLAY
                         ==========
  The overall aim of the game is to assasinate to leader of a rebel
  faction on an alien planet. There is also a puzzle element.
  Strategically placed computer terminals & floor pads for entry. Passes
  can  be obtained by meeting Spies, shooting baddies or rescuing hotages.
  If you choose a PC with a high electronics rating you may bypass
  some of these terminals automaticaly. Alternatively a PC with a high
  weapons rating may be able to blow out the doors.
  Pass cards dropped by antagonists will give access to some stores & doors.
  Warp stations  will place the PCs on different parts on map.

                         GAME HISTORY
                         ============
  Development of this project began in Late March 1995. We were so
  impressed by CD rom as a mutlimedia tool that we began developing
  for this exciting medium. We traveled to the spring E.C.T.S to find
  that most Major Developers & Publishers were deserting the Amiga &
  CD32 formats & were developing for other formats.
  As we already had code & design nearly finished, we carried on
  developing in the hope of a satisfactory end to the long
  running Commodore saga.

  With most major publishers not willing to support CD Rom Amiga
  development we release this playable demo to test the Amiga Market.
  To see if it is worth continuing with the Amiga Version of this game....

